'''Peter Serafinowicz''' ([[July 10]], [[1972]])<ref name="This Week" /> is an English actor, voice actor, comedian and writer. Serafinowicz was the first actor to provide the voice for [[Maul|Darth Maul]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']].

He also provided the voice for a [[Gungan]] scout and [[2163]] but wasn't credited for it in the film. Serafinowcz did initial recordings as Maul for ''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]'', but was replaced by [[Sam Witwer]], who had voiced the character in ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' and ''[[Star Wars Rebels]]''.<ref name="Serafinowicz Cut from Solo">{{YouTube|video=NkekOiFrnYg|text=Peter Serafinowicz Tells the Story of How He Was Cut Out as Darth Maul in Solo|channel=channel/UC-SDiZLNHzanQ4xDtwoFkSA|name=Collider Podcasts}}</ref>

